ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported
List as many words beginning with the letter F within 1 minute; other letters may also be used. Record the number of correct words
List as many words beginning with the letter A within 1 minute; other letters may also be used. Record the number of correct words
List as many words beginning with the letter S within 1 minute; other letters may also be used. Record the number of correct words

ElementDescription: "Verbal Fluency (7y+): Phonemic category comprised of letters A, F, and S total number of words credited"

Notes: List as many words of things in the kitchen within 1 minute; other categories may be used. Record the number of correct words
List as many animals within 1 minute; other categories may be used. Record the number of correct words
Total number of correct words in the given category within 60 seconds

ElementDescription: Written Fluency: Part A- Letter S
Notes: Write down as many words beginning with the Letter S within 5 minutes; other letters may be used. Record the number of correct words

ElementDescription: Written Fluency: Part B- Letter C (only 4 letters)
Notes: Write down as many words beginning with the Letter C and containing only four letters within 4 minutes; other letters may be used. Record the number of correct words

ElementDescription: Written Fluency: Sum of correct words for Part A and Part B
List as many words beginning with the letter C within 1 minute. Record the number of correct words
List as many words beginning with the letter L within 1 minute. Record the number of correct words
Scaled score based off of percentile
